Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - RITA: Detect beaconing traffic

Detect beaconing traffic

The strength of RITA is undeniable when detecting C2 communications, especially with those agents that communicate to masters with a fixed communication interval (0% jitter). 

In the demo, we will detect Octopus traffic which uses HTTPS as a communication channel between the agent and the master server. 

To do that, you will need to repeat the steps demonstrated in the previous demo: converting the PCAP into Zeek logs and importing them into the RITA database for analysis. Open your terminal, then execute the following:

  • cd ~/Desktop/CCD/RITA/pcap
  • mkdir octopus_logs && cd octopus_logs
  • zeek -r ../octopus.pcap local && cd ..
  • sudo rita import octopus_logs octopus

Now comes the fun part, which is spotting the C2 traffic, and to do that, go ahead and execute the following command:

sudo rita show-beacons octopus
